Package com.pb.sawdust.util.array

Provides utilities for working with arrays.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    TypeSafeArray<T>
    The TypeSafeArray interface provides a wrapper for arrays so that they may be parameterized like other generic classes.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ArrayUtil
    The ArrayUtil class provides a variety of static convenience methods for dealing with arrays.
    BooleanTypeSafeArray
    The BooleanTypeSafeArray provides a type safe wrapper for (possibly multidimensional) boolean arrays.
    ByteTypeSafeArray
    The ByteypeSafeArray provides a type safe wrapper for (possibly multidimensional) byte arrays.
    CharTypeSafeArray
    The CharTypeSafeArray provides a type safe wrapper for (possibly multidimensional) char arrays.
    DoubleTypeSafeArray
    The DoubleTypeSafeArray provides a type safe wrapper for (possibly multidimensional) boolean arrays.
    FloatTypeSafeArray
    The FloatTypeSafeArray provides a type safe wrapper for (possibly multidimensional) float arrays.
    IntTypeSafeArray
    The IntTypeSafeArray provides a type safe wrapper for (possibly multidimensional) int arrays.
    LongTypeSafeArray
    The LongTypeSafeArray provides a type safe wrapper for (possibly multidimensional) long arrays.
    ObjectTypeSafeArray<T>
    The ObjectTypeSafeArray provides a wrapper for object arrays (possibly multidimensional) which are parameterized with the type of the array.
    ShortTypeSafeArray
    The ShortTypeSafeArray provides a type safe wrapper for (possibly multidimensional) short arrays.
    TypeSafeArrayFactory
    The TypeSafeArrayFactory holds static methods which provide TypeSafeArray implementations.

Package com.pb.sawdust.util.array Description

Provides utilities for working with arrays. It includes a blanket ArrayUtil class as well as a series of classes allowing parameterization of arrays and better type-safety with primitive and multi-dimensional arrays.
